      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ELLE PERFECTO (6) made a winning start for Luke McCarthy when she overcame a wide draw and a handy field for a 2m win at this circuit last week. Gives away 30m at the handicap this time and tackles older rivals but last week's win was her first hitout for four months and she should be better for it. ITZFERGIETIME (9) has the hoof on the till after placing in her two starts here since a spell, last week finishing second and just 1.5 metres from the winner. Three-time third-up winner so should be close to her peak now. There was plenty of merit in the resuming effort of ADDICTIVE STRIDE (2) who drew wide and raced three wide without cover but stuck on for a respectable second at this venue. Can progress off that. VALTINO (10) hasn't raced since he was fourth to wonder mare in the Group 1 Great Square in Brisbane last December but goes well fresh and has been readied with two trials. Cops a 40m handicap but he is accomplished.",
